<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 7:02PM MDT  by NWS Billings</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Rosebud
County through 745 PM MDT...
At 701 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Lame Deer, or 26 miles south of Colstrip, moving north
at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail and heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lame Deer and Northern Cheyenne Indian Reservation.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
